Ephemeral  

Life teases death  
With beauty that blooms,  
Like these flowers in despair,  
Raising their lovely heads,  
To the soft caress of sunlight  
Before they wither,  
Yet the memory of  
Their fleeting grace lingers.

- Jean Toomer
